(Fig. 5). Ovipositor short, conical; apophyses anteriores short and thin, wide based; apophyses posteriores relatively long and stout, four times longer then apophyses anteriores. Antrum long, wide, heavily sclerotized; ductus bursae similarly sclerotised, with narrow membranous ring (
"neck"
